name: politico
text: During an event today, Joe Biden called on President Trump to officially attribute the massive cyberattack that’s affected numerous government agencies and hold those responsible for it accountable https://t.co/ZeYjC9Bv0o https://t.co/7Yf7HNm2WU

name: politico
text: President Donald Trump issued pardons today to two former Republican congressmen who pleaded guilty to felony charges, as well as the campaign operative whose contacts with a Russian-aligned academic triggered the Trump-Russia investigation in 2016 https://t.co/R2euyeFTp3

name: politico
text:

name: politico
text: Trump has been strategizing in recent days with a band of his fiercest congressional supporters about lodging objections during the typically pro forma congressional certification of President-elect Joe Biden’s victory https://t.co/QJ2jD5UUrJ

name: politico
text:
Democrats settled for a smaller bill with no money for state and local governments. Republicans spent more than they wanted. 

Here’s how the second-largest stimulus deal ever was reached:

name: politico
text:
Forget that $900 billion relief package. 

Joe Biden and Mitch McConnell are already thinking about the next one, which could double as the first legislative showdown of the coming Biden presidency. https://t.co/3KqgAHOUcn

name: politico
text: President Trump blasted the $900 billion coronavirus relief package passed by Congress, calling it a “disgrace” and asking for amendments to the bill to increase stimulus payments to Americans https://t.co/fZl2fZnP7u

name: politico
text: President Donald Trump announced plans today to appoint another slate of top allies to various government boards, yet another sign that his time in office is winding to a close https://t.co/tqoNSx6ewt

name: politico
text: A lawyer for states seeking to preserve the DACA program asked a federal judge to hold off ruling on a legal challenge to the arrangement until President-elect Joe Biden is sworn in https://t.co/KEAvUlnUg4

name: politico
text: The long-sought money is on its way — but state and local officials worry that it could take several months for it to reach communities in need https://t.co/VIzNe4OF29

name: politico
text:
The leaders of the House Intelligence Committee have been the faces of some of Capitol Hill’s most public partisan brawls of Trump’s presidency.

Now they’re widely expected to be reappointed to their respective roles in the 117th Congress. https://t.co/HZXMWCI2lQ

name: politico
text: An election systems worker driven into hiding by death threats has filed a defamation lawsuit against President Donald Trump’s campaign, two of its lawyers and some conservative media figures and outlets https://t.co/OrnxXSmi6k

name: politico
text: Just when we all thought we could pack up and slide into a desperately needed Christmas break, President Trump tossed a grenade into the Covid relief bill calling the $900B package passed by both houses of Congress a “disgrace” https://t.co/etCXoOm33N

name: politico
text:
President Trump had a busy night. 

In one night he:
• issued a raft of pre-Christmas pardons and commutations
• endorsed a primary challenge to Sen. John Thune (R-S.D.)
• took aim at the Covid-relief bill, threatening a veto
